<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>About</title>
    <style>
        .about_container{
            padding: 4rem 0rem 0rem 10rem;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            top: 5rem;
            position: relative;
            & div{
                margin-bottom: 3rem;
                padding-left: 2rem;
            }
        }
        h1{
            font-size: 2.2rem;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
        }
        p{
            font-size: 1.6rem;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            background: rgba(81, 219, 70, 0.1);
            width: 65rem;
            padding: 1rem;
        }

    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <%- include("header") %>
    <section class="about_container">
        <h1>about :</h1>
        <div class="about_div">
            <p>Hide Here is a tiny, focused app built to help you store short pieces of text that matter<br> — links, quick to-dos, copy snippets, reminders, and anything else you want to hide in<br> a safe, easy-to-access spot. No noise, no complicated folders<br> — just fast text storage that gets out of your way and helps you get back to what matters.</p>
        </div>

        <h1>Why we built it :</h1>
        <div class="why_built">
            <p>
                We noticed people using messy notes, long email threads, or dozens of browser tabs <br>to hold onto small but important bits of text. Hide Here gives you a clean, single place <br>to stash those things so they’re searchable, shareable (if you want), and available across devices.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

</body>
</html>